00:20:38.705 --> 00:20:42.413
That night, one more Pomeranian
turned into an Alsatian.


257
00:20:42.496 --> 00:20:44.621
God's powder was magic.

258
00:20:44.705 --> 00:20:47.205
My confidence was sky-rocketing.

259
00:20:50.080 --> 00:20:52.330
-Where's the bottle?
-Your dad chucked it.


260
00:20:53.996 --> 00:20:57.788
Damn! For how long will he control me?

261
00:20:58.705 --> 00:21:01.705
My father controlled me for 60 years.

262
00:21:02.288 --> 00:21:04.330
-How did he let go?
-He popped it.


263
00:21:07.413 --> 00:21:09.705
Dudes, don't leave. 
The vodka's coming.

264
00:21:09.788 --> 00:21:11.996
The bar's closed, Sanju.

265
00:21:12.080 --> 00:21:15.830
Dad thinks cutting supply
will make us quit?


266
00:21:16.163 --> 00:21:17.996
I have a back-up daddy

267
00:21:18.121 --> 00:21:20.288
who'll fill up our mugs.

268
00:21:20.371 --> 00:21:23.080
-Back-up dad?
-My girlfriend's pop.


269
00:21:37.205 --> 00:21:38.455
Is daddy home?

270
00:21:38.996 --> 00:21:41.455
Yes, don't sneak in through the balcony.

271
00:21:42.038 --> 00:21:44.371
I'll ring the doorbell. Wake him.

272
00:21:46.496 --> 00:21:47.746
At this hour?

273
00:21:49.121 --> 00:21:50.496
What's so important?

274
00:21:51.830 --> 00:21:53.621
I want something, baby.

275
00:21:58.580 --> 00:22:01.371
I'll be there in five. 
Open the door.

276
00:22:10.413 --> 00:22:11.788
Wake up your dad.

277
00:22:17.205 --> 00:22:21.746
Dad, mom... wake up. Sanju's here.

278
00:22:21.830 --> 00:22:24.038
At 1 a.m.? Is everything okay?

279
00:22:24.121 --> 00:22:26.288
Took him six months to muster courage.

280
00:22:26.371 --> 00:22:29.038
He'd said, once his career kick started,

281
00:22:29.163 --> 00:22:31.663
he'll ask for my hand.

282
00:22:31.746 --> 00:22:34.621
Just the hand, or all of you?

283
00:22:38.330 --> 00:22:40.288
We'll ask for the 18-year-old scotch.

284
00:22:40.496 --> 00:22:41.913
Will the old fart agree?

285
00:22:42.038 --> 00:22:44.955
If he doesn't agree, we grab and flee!

286
00:22:47.163 --> 00:22:49.246
Hello, child. How are you?

287
00:22:49.580 --> 00:22:53.455
Before you ask for anything,
I have something for you.


288
00:22:58.496 --> 00:22:59.330
Ten rupees?

289
00:22:59.913 --> 00:23:02.746
My father's gift to me
when I joined the Navy.


290
00:23:02.830 --> 00:23:06.246
He said, "There are two kinds of bills."

291
00:23:06.580 --> 00:23:09.038
"Real and fake."

292
00:23:09.288 --> 00:23:12.080
When you tug at a real bill...

293
00:23:14.330 --> 00:23:15.455
it won't tear.

294
00:23:16.455 --> 00:23:18.788
You're starting your career.

295
00:23:18.871 --> 00:23:22.080
Life will pull you left and right.

296
00:23:22.163 --> 00:23:27.538
But if you stay honest,
nothing can rip you apart.


297
00:23:29.163 --> 00:23:32.288
My father's wisdom is now yours.

298
00:23:32.830 --> 00:23:34.371
Homi, let him sit.

299
00:23:34.455 --> 00:23:36.121
Sit.

300
00:23:37.080 --> 00:23:38.621
Now tell us.

301
00:23:38.871 --> 00:23:40.746
What brings you here?

302
00:23:42.996 --> 00:23:47.871
The real reason we're here is...
we have the midnight urge.


303
00:23:50.455 --> 00:23:51.830
Can't control it anymore.

304
00:23:57.371 --> 00:24:00.746
Look, we're weak with idioms.

305
00:24:01.455 --> 00:24:04.371
Tell us clearly, what's a "midnight urge"?

306
00:24:04.455 --> 00:24:06.288
Midnight urge means...

307
00:24:13.080 --> 00:24:15.496
I'm 21 now. It's a biological need.

308
00:24:15.663 --> 00:24:19.371
As soon as midnight strikes...
the urge surges.


309
00:24:19.830 --> 00:24:23.788
I need it now... or I'm gonna explode!

310
00:24:24.746 --> 00:24:27.038
But dad doesn't allow it.

311
00:24:27.288 --> 00:24:30.330
He's orthodox. 
So I sin in secret.

312
00:24:31.038 --> 00:24:34.580
Once, I was enjoying an 18-year-old
on the terrace... dad walked in.


313
00:24:34.663 --> 00:24:38.413
I told him frankly, "Dad, I'm an adult.

314
00:24:38.496 --> 00:24:41.705
My friends do it every night.
Their parents never object."


315
00:24:41.955 --> 00:24:46.246
He said, "Alright, have your 18-year-old.
But don't hide.


316
00:24:46.330 --> 00:24:49.080
Do it openly on the dining table,
before the family.


317
00:24:49.163 --> 00:24:51.580
And that too, only once a month."

318
00:24:51.663 --> 00:24:54.413
Daddy, how will once a month
quench this thirst?


319
00:24:54.955 --> 00:24:56.871
Now I frequent the illicit joints.

320
00:24:56.955 --> 00:24:59.538
16, 18, 21...
I grab whatever is available.


321
00:25:00.038 --> 00:25:05.163
I park on a lonely stretch,
and indulge in the backseat.


322
00:25:05.246 --> 00:25:06.913
Only fear is the cops.

323
00:25:07.413 --> 00:25:09.746
They peek when you're about to peak.

324
00:25:10.038 --> 00:25:12.413
Ma'am, try the backseat.

325
00:25:15.246 --> 00:25:17.746
You were a Navy Captain.

326
00:25:17.830 --> 00:25:21.080
You must've tasted the best
on every shore.


327
00:25:22.705 --> 00:25:27.413
Be kind, let us
taste some from your home.

328
00:25:29.788 --> 00:25:32.038
-May we get one each?
-What!


329
00:25:32.455 --> 00:25:33.746
Okay, we'll share one.

330
00:25:35.955 --> 00:25:38.705
When daddy gets the urge,
you happily serve.


331
00:25:38.996 --> 00:25:42.746
All we get is a "How dare you!"
Sorry, I've promised my friend.


332
00:25:42.830 --> 00:25:45.913
I'm gonna grab one.

333
00:25:46.038 --> 00:25:48.246
Stop!

334
00:25:51.163 --> 00:25:52.163
Soda or water?

335
00:25:57.913 --> 00:25:59.705
And return my papa's box.

336
00:26:03.621 --> 00:26:05.038
Can I say something?

337
00:26:06.121 --> 00:26:08.705
Your papa was wrong.

338
00:26:08.788 --> 00:26:13.871
Life doesn't just pull you left and right.

339
00:26:14.496 --> 00:26:17.496
It also pulls you up and down.

340
00:26:29.621 --> 00:26:31.871
I drank all night with my friends.

341
00:26:32.413 --> 00:26:33.996
And returned home in the morning.

342
00:26:44.788 --> 00:26:46.621
I'm going for a jog.

343
00:26:54.788 --> 00:26:55.663
Sit.

344
00:27:00.038 --> 00:27:03.246
Sorry, sonny. I yelled at you publicly.

345
00:27:03.871 --> 00:27:08.455
I'm stressed, so couldn't control myself.

346
00:27:10.163 --> 00:27:11.246
A request...

347
00:27:12.538 --> 00:27:15.080
Please focus on your work.

348
00:27:15.163 --> 00:27:18.830
Your mother should feel proud
when she sees your first film.


349
00:27:19.913 --> 00:27:23.621
She may not be
able to see your next.

350
00:27:24.788 --> 00:27:25.621
Why?

351
00:27:30.038 --> 00:27:32.496
She has cancer of the pancreas.

352
00:27:33.205 --> 00:27:36.955
I'm taking her to New York.
Sloan Hospital.


353
00:27:37.038 --> 00:27:39.788
Why didn't anyone tell me?

354
00:27:39.871 --> 00:27:43.330
She hid it from you
so your work won't suffer.


355
00:27:43.746 --> 00:27:46.455
She's been in pain all year.

356
00:27:46.913 --> 00:27:49.413
But acts fit in front of you.

357
00:27:49.496 --> 00:27:51.163
Where are you?

358
00:27:51.871 --> 00:27:54.080
In the dining. 
Want some tea?

359
00:27:54.163 --> 00:27:55.413
Half a cup.

360
00:27:55.830 --> 00:27:56.955
Hide it.

361
00:27:59.163 --> 00:28:00.580
Don't cry in her presence.

362
00:28:00.663 --> 00:28:03.663
She's acting. So must you.

363
00:28:05.121 --> 00:28:07.663
Up so early?

364
00:28:09.038 --> 00:28:11.413
Did you tell Sanju
we're off to New York?

365
00:28:12.538 --> 00:28:15.830
What? Haven't shared the news?

366
00:28:17.163 --> 00:28:20.830
Take a deep breath.
You're gonna be shocked.


367
00:28:22.163 --> 00:28:25.205
I've been offered a Hollywood film.

368
00:28:25.996 --> 00:28:28.413
Now I'll mouth English dialogues.

369
00:28:30.996 --> 00:28:32.663
James Bond.

370
00:28:45.205 --> 00:28:48.246
I wish they had songs like our films.

371
00:28:48.705 --> 00:28:52.663
This heart has lost its mate

372
00:28:53.163 --> 00:28:57.246
No one knows where my liver went

373
00:28:58.121 --> 00:29:01.038
A song here, a dance there,

374
00:29:01.288 --> 00:29:03.080
and the Oscar's mine!

375
00:29:03.788 --> 00:29:05.871
You shouldn't have retired!

376
00:29:05.955 --> 00:29:08.996
Retired? I still act, don't I?

377
00:29:31.080 --> 00:29:33.080
Dad took mom to New York.

378
00:29:33.163 --> 00:29:35.621
And I started spending more time with God.

379
00:29:37.788 --> 00:29:41.955
I was 18 when I lost my parents
in a car crash.


380
00:29:42.038 --> 00:29:44.538
I was going to kill myself.

381
00:29:44.955 --> 00:29:47.080
A fakir saved me.

382
00:29:47.330 --> 00:29:51.246
He said, "The Lord who created pain,
also created a remedy."


383
00:29:51.913 --> 00:29:52.913
Here.

384
00:29:53.121 --> 00:29:56.163
Put it under your tongue.
It'll melt away all pain.


385
00:29:56.246 --> 00:29:59.455
He gets it from the Himalayas.
So it's expensive.


386
00:29:59.621 --> 00:30:01.996
But I'll send him the money.

387
00:30:28.288 --> 00:30:31.996
The first time I did drugs,
was 'cause I was upset with dad.


388
00:30:32.413 --> 00:30:35.246
The second time, 'cause mom was dying.

389
00:30:36.580 --> 00:30:39.830
By the third time, 
I was an addict.

390
00:30:42.205 --> 00:30:44.913
Then I got the news
that mom was in a coma.


391
00:30:45.038 --> 00:30:47.330
Dad summoned me to America.

392
00:30:47.413 --> 00:30:49.455
I traveled with my sisters...

393
00:30:49.621 --> 00:30:51.496
and 20 grams of cocaine.

394
00:30:54.705 --> 00:30:57.080
Being caught at the airport,
would've meant


395
00:30:57.413 --> 00:31:00.913
20 years in prison... even for my sisters.

396
00:31:01.496 --> 00:31:03.330
But back then, 20 years in prison,

397
00:31:03.413 --> 00:31:05.038
versus 20 grams of cocaine...

398
00:31:05.288 --> 00:31:07.330
my choice was crystal clear.

399
00:31:09.080 --> 00:31:11.121
I was so irresponsible

400
00:31:11.330 --> 00:31:13.371
that instead of spending time with mom,

401
00:31:13.455 --> 00:31:16.205
I'd smoke away in the fire exit.

402
00:31:16.455 --> 00:31:19.580
Then one night, walked into my life...

403
00:31:21.080 --> 00:31:23.955
Mr. Kamlesh Kanhaiyalal Kapasi.

404
00:31:42.830 --> 00:31:45.705
-What did you steal?
-Twins...


405
00:31:46.205 --> 00:31:50.080
-O Lord Ganesha!
-This is Jesus' jurisdiction.


406
00:31:50.496 --> 00:31:53.496
Lord Ganesha doesn't operate here.
What did you steal?


407
00:31:53.830 --> 00:31:56.996
I'd gone to keep the idol inside.

408
00:32:07.371 --> 00:32:11.330
I'm a fan of your parents.

409
00:32:11.996 --> 00:32:14.830
Thought Lord Ganesha
will heal your mother.


410
00:32:18.996 --> 00:32:20.163
But, what's "Twins"?

411
00:32:21.621 --> 00:32:24.705
Eggs. Back home we call them Twins.

412
00:32:27.413 --> 00:32:29.371
Hope "The Twins" haven't parted ways.

413
00:32:29.746 --> 00:32:30.996
They are out of shape.

414
00:32:33.413 --> 00:32:34.330
Come.

415
00:32:35.080 --> 00:32:37.955
-Where?
-To get The Twins back in shape.


416
00:33:15.205 --> 00:33:16.996
Ever seen a topless girl?

417
00:33:17.330 --> 00:33:19.080
Of course, I have.

418
00:33:19.413 --> 00:33:22.163
-Where? On TV?
-No, live.


419
00:33:22.371 --> 00:33:25.996
My physics teacher, back home...

420
00:33:26.413 --> 00:33:28.455
his mother slipped in the bathroom.

421
00:33:28.580 --> 00:33:31.538
I broke the door,
hauled her on my shoulder


422
00:33:31.621 --> 00:33:33.163
and put her in the ambulance.

423
00:33:33.330 --> 00:33:36.080
Stark naked... topless, bottomless.

424
00:33:36.371 --> 00:33:38.205
How old was she?

425
00:33:38.288 --> 00:33:39.913
Ninety. No, 91.

426
00:33:42.496 --> 00:33:44.205
I did see stuff. 
I'm not naive.

427
00:33:44.955 --> 00:33:47.288
-Ever had alcohol?
-Of course.


428
00:34:11.955 --> 00:34:13.788
There's a saying back home...

429
00:34:13.913 --> 00:34:16.163
"Jam-jam bam-bam."

430
00:34:16.663 --> 00:34:17.746
Translate that.

431
00:34:18.163 --> 00:34:19.746
"Jam-jam" is money.

432
00:34:19.955 --> 00:34:21.746
And "bam-bam"?

433
00:34:23.163 --> 00:34:24.413
Sex.

434
00:34:26.330 --> 00:34:30.080
Your jacket took away jam-jam,
I lost my bam-bam.


435
00:34:30.496 --> 00:34:33.288
You owe me a blonde.

436
00:34:39.246 --> 00:34:40.913
Cover me.

437
00:34:52.413 --> 00:34:53.663
Don't! You'll land in prison.

438
00:34:53.746 --> 00:34:55.163
Relax.

439
00:35:49.746 --> 00:35:50.746
Run!

440
00:36:06.330 --> 00:36:08.496
Stop joking. We could've been arrested.

441
00:36:08.663 --> 00:36:10.913
Noble cause, brother.

442
00:36:13.538 --> 00:36:17.538
Your mom's in the hospital
and you're snorting?


443
00:36:17.746 --> 00:36:19.955
Hey, Mr. Righteousness.

444
00:36:20.121 --> 00:36:22.121
We've been friends for just five minutes.

445
00:36:22.705 --> 00:36:25.413
-Control your emotions.
-Friendship?


446
00:36:25.705 --> 00:36:29.246
You aren't a good son!
How'll you be a good friend?


447
00:36:33.913 --> 00:36:36.121
Get lost! I don't need a friend.

448
00:36:43.163 --> 00:36:44.538
Hey, stop!

449
00:36:52.205 --> 00:36:53.746
I just can't quit.

450
00:36:58.705 --> 00:37:00.121
Alright, go!

451
00:37:00.746 --> 00:37:05.080
If my friend was on drugs,
I wouldn't abandon him.


452
00:37:05.163 --> 00:37:06.746
I'd thrash him till he quit.

453
00:37:16.330 --> 00:37:17.455
Throw it.

454
00:37:17.538 --> 00:37:20.080
-I'll quit tomorrow.
-Now.


455
00:37:20.246 --> 00:37:21.830
I promise, tomorrow.

456
00:37:22.913 --> 00:37:25.705
-Let go my twins.
-Let go the powder.


457
00:37:25.996 --> 00:37:28.163
-Twins first.
-Powder first.


458
00:37:28.455 --> 00:37:30.871
-I'm desperate.
-It's the time to fight.


459
00:37:31.246 --> 00:37:32.496
Say, "I'm a tiger."

460
00:37:32.705 --> 00:37:34.163
-Now, rorr.
-"Rorr"?


461
00:37:36.163 --> 00:37:36.996
Once more.

462
00:37:41.455 --> 00:37:44.496
I quit! I promise.

463
00:37:46.955 --> 00:37:51.038
Never abandon me, Master.
Such words of wisdom...


464
00:37:51.371 --> 00:37:54.705
Rorr, jam-jam bam-bam, twins.

465
00:37:55.705 --> 00:37:57.163
Guess what?

466
00:37:57.288 --> 00:37:58.830
You didn't twist my twins...

467
00:37:59.913 --> 00:38:01.038
but this.

468
00:38:09.913 --> 00:38:12.163
I was seeking drugs in New York.

469
00:38:12.246 --> 00:38:14.080
Instead, I found a friend.

470
00:38:14.163 --> 00:38:17.413
Kamlesh Kanhaiyalal Kapasi.
They call me Kamli.


471
00:38:17.621 --> 00:38:21.455
As Sex-spear has said, "What's in a name?"

472
00:38:21.996 --> 00:38:24.580
-Who?
-Sex-spear.


473
00:38:25.246 --> 00:38:26.705
William...

474
00:38:27.288 --> 00:38:29.580
-Sir, will you have snakes?
-Snakes?


475
00:38:29.871 --> 00:38:32.163
Snakes. There are lots in the hole.

476
00:38:32.955 --> 00:38:34.205
I'll get it, sir.

477
00:38:38.830 --> 00:38:42.830
In his accent, snacks were "snakes"
and hall was "hole".


478
00:38:43.080 --> 00:38:46.121
He brought back our smiles.

479
00:38:46.205 --> 00:38:51.163
And miraculously,
his idol got mom out of coma.


480
00:38:51.371 --> 00:38:52.913
Ready, everyone?

481
00:38:53.246 --> 00:38:55.080
Smile.

482
00:39:10.621 --> 00:39:15.371
At your film premiere,
I'll sit between father and son.


483
00:39:16.205 --> 00:39:19.455
As you appear on screen, I'll whistle.

484
00:39:24.288 --> 00:39:28.205
At your wedding, 
I'll dance on the table.

485
00:39:28.580 --> 00:39:30.663
Warn Ruby not to be embarrassed.

486
00:39:33.663 --> 00:39:38.413
Mom didn't know Ruby wasn't talking to me.

487
00:39:42.913 --> 00:39:44.621
Mom didn't have much time left.

488
00:39:45.038 --> 00:39:46.413
I decided

489
00:39:46.496 --> 00:39:50.705
I'd apologize to Ruby's dad
and ask for her hand.


490
00:39:51.413 --> 00:39:53.163
I love Ruby and I want to...

491
00:39:56.205 --> 00:39:57.996
I've come to apologize.

492
00:39:58.288 --> 00:40:01.205
-I misbehaved that day.
-It's alright, child.


493
00:40:01.371 --> 00:40:03.371
-A tipple often does that.
-No, Daddy.


494
00:40:03.955 --> 00:40:07.121
I wasn't just drunk...
I had also done cocaine.


495
00:40:07.580 --> 00:40:13.913
Let me confess. 
The next day I did LSD.

496
00:40:14.288 --> 00:40:16.538
But I've been clean for a month.

497
00:40:19.038 --> 00:40:20.163
Congratulations!

498
00:40:25.038 --> 00:40:26.330
I'll go meet Ruby.

499
00:40:27.163 --> 00:40:29.371
-Ruby.
-Wait.


500
00:40:29.705 --> 00:40:32.371
Meet her on the 22nd
at Hotel Sun and Sand,


501
00:40:32.455 --> 00:40:34.496
with these flowers.

502
00:40:34.955 --> 00:40:36.913
-What's on the 22nd?
-Wait.


503
00:40:43.955 --> 00:40:46.205
That's for your parents.

504
00:40:46.371 --> 00:40:48.455
And that's for you. 
Write your name.

505
00:40:48.538 --> 00:40:51.371
"Ruby weds..." Who's this Rustom?

506
00:40:54.538 --> 00:40:58.455
All this for a 10 rupee bill?
I'll glue it up.


507
00:40:58.538 --> 00:41:02.496
I'm glad you tore it. 
It led us to Rustom!

508
00:41:02.580 --> 00:41:05.830
He's a doctor in New York.
Not a junkie like you.


509
00:41:07.080 --> 00:41:08.455
Daddy, let me meet Ruby--

510
00:41:14.246 --> 00:41:16.496
Then what should I call you? Old fart?

511
00:41:16.913 --> 00:41:20.496
Meet Ruby over my dead body.

