Dutt's orders.

1290
01:47:10.830 --> 01:47:16.913
Tell the Court, you knew about
the bomb blast conspiracy.


1291
01:47:19.705 --> 01:47:20.871
Kamlesh,

1292
01:47:21.205 --> 01:47:22.455
please wait outside.

1293
01:47:38.121 --> 01:47:39.121
Where are you going?

1294
01:47:39.955 --> 01:47:42.413
FBI raided my office.

1295
01:47:43.163 --> 01:47:44.163
Why?

1296
01:47:49.621 --> 01:47:51.830
What's that got to do with the FBI?

1297
01:47:53.080 --> 01:47:55.830
My company works with
the American government.


1298
01:47:56.163 --> 01:47:58.413
Now they'll investigate our association.

1299
01:47:59.038 --> 01:48:00.996
Terror charges freak them out.

1300
01:48:04.288 --> 01:48:05.288
Sorry, buddy.

1301
01:48:06.330 --> 01:48:08.080
I've put you through all this...

1302
01:48:09.705 --> 01:48:14.080
-Call me when you get there.
-No... my phone will be tapped.


1303
01:48:15.913 --> 01:48:18.288
We must disconnect for a few years.

1304
01:48:21.038 --> 01:48:24.038
Don't worry. I understand. Go...

1305
01:48:25.663 --> 01:48:27.871
Hey, Kamli. You're a tiger.

1306
01:48:36.330 --> 01:48:37.538
Let's go.

1307
01:48:47.955 --> 01:48:50.330
First time ever I lied to Sanju.

1308
01:48:50.413 --> 01:48:52.205
I can be friends with an addict.

1309
01:48:52.996 --> 01:48:58.746
Even with a guy who slept with my girl.
But with a terrorist? I'm no fool!


1310
01:49:01.371 --> 01:49:04.246
Every time I drink, I miss him...

1311
01:49:04.871 --> 01:49:06.288
yearn to call him.

1312
01:49:07.705 --> 01:49:09.580
Then I remind myself...

1313
01:49:10.496 --> 01:49:13.788
there was a truck full of RDX
at his house.


1314
01:49:13.871 --> 01:49:15.663
He's a bloody terrorist!

1315
01:49:17.788 --> 01:49:19.038
Are we done?

1316
01:49:22.913 --> 01:49:24.038
Mail from Winnie.

1317
01:49:24.580 --> 01:49:25.705
Where's she?

1318
01:49:26.788 --> 01:49:27.621
America.

1319
01:49:28.996 --> 01:49:30.163
She won't write the book.

1320
01:49:33.663 --> 01:49:36.288
Sanjay Dutt was given 30 days
to surrender.


1321
01:49:36.455 --> 01:49:37.788
That time is over.

1322
01:49:37.955 --> 01:49:42.205
He's on his way to prison.

1323
01:49:42.788 --> 01:49:43.746
Clothes off.

1324
01:49:44.746 --> 01:49:45.913
Raise your hands.

1325
01:49:48.746 --> 01:49:49.955
Turn.

1326
01:49:54.121 --> 01:49:55.121
Bend.

1327
01:49:57.705 --> 01:49:58.871
Cough.

1328
01:49:59.455 --> 01:50:00.621
Harder.

1329
01:50:40.080 --> 01:50:43.038
You dropped Sanju's story
for a book on museums?


1330
01:50:45.580 --> 01:50:49.205
-Museums don't lie.
-Nor did Sanju.


1331
01:50:49.580 --> 01:50:53.455
But a news report
became your gospel truth.


1332
01:50:56.038 --> 01:50:57.038
What's this?

1333
01:50:57.705 --> 01:51:00.996
Prison has a community radio
for prisoners' reform.


1334
01:51:01.413 --> 01:51:03.830
Sanju hosts a show.

1335
01:51:04.330 --> 01:51:06.746
He wants you to hear this episode.

1336
01:51:06.955 --> 01:51:08.496
Took great pains to smuggle it out.

1337
01:51:12.996 --> 01:51:14.205
My number.

1338
01:51:14.538 --> 01:51:16.538
You'll need it after you're done.

1339
01:51:30.913 --> 01:51:33.205
Howdy, Yerwada!

1340
01:51:33.288 --> 01:51:37.830
This is your buddy, Sanju!

1341
01:51:41.871 --> 01:51:46.371
Today's topic is "newspapers."

1342
01:51:47.038 --> 01:51:50.080
There were no newspapers 400 years ago.

1343
01:51:50.413 --> 01:51:52.205
News traveled word of mouth.

1344
01:51:52.288 --> 01:51:54.455
Then, someone printed the first newspaper.

1345
01:51:54.580 --> 01:51:57.913
Soon, selling news became big business.

1346
01:51:58.288 --> 01:52:04.830
Today, India has 105,437
registered publications,


1347
01:52:05.288 --> 01:52:08.413
thousands of radio stations,
TV channels and the internet.


1348
01:52:09.121 --> 01:52:11.663
And they're in a rat race...

1349
01:52:12.580 --> 01:52:14.705
fighting for readership.

1350
01:52:15.121 --> 01:52:18.413
More readers means more money from ads.

1351
01:52:19.496 --> 01:52:23.538
And how do you lure readers?
With the truth?


1352
01:52:24.913 --> 01:52:25.830
No.

1353
01:52:26.621 --> 01:52:29.496
With news that's spicy!

1354
01:52:30.580 --> 01:52:33.496
And how do you do that?

1355
01:52:34.080 --> 01:52:35.955
Easy! With a question mark.

1356
01:52:38.663 --> 01:52:44.663
When I was on bail,
these question marks were on my tail.


1357
01:52:44.746 --> 01:52:46.413
SANJU IN A BRAWL?

1358
01:52:51.371 --> 01:52:53.163
SANJU SOZZLED?

1359
01:52:56.288 --> 01:52:59.913
Dad decided to fight back.

1360
01:52:59.996 --> 01:53:02.705
Mr. Dutt, what a surprise!

1361
01:53:02.788 --> 01:53:04.830
How many pages does your paper have?

1362
01:53:05.746 --> 01:53:07.705
-Twenty four.
-Cut it down to eight.


1363
01:53:08.746 --> 01:53:11.746
Then you won't need
fake news to fill pages.


1364
01:53:12.413 --> 01:53:13.746
Please come.

1365
01:53:15.746 --> 01:53:20.996
If our reportage bothers you, sue us.

1366
01:53:22.621 --> 01:53:24.538
How can I fight you?

1367
01:53:24.621 --> 01:53:26.246
You have James Bond with you.

1368
01:53:27.121 --> 01:53:28.038
James Bond?

1369
01:53:28.121 --> 01:53:31.121
James Bond has a license to kill.

1370
01:53:31.413 --> 01:53:34.288
He has legal immunity.

1371
01:53:34.496 --> 01:53:37.163
Similarly, you have these question marks.

1372
01:53:37.496 --> 01:53:40.330
In Court, you'll state,
"This isn't confirmed news."


1373
01:53:40.413 --> 01:53:43.746
"Just speculation.
Don't miss the question mark."


1374
01:53:43.830 --> 01:53:45.580
"According to sources..."

1375
01:53:48.788 --> 01:53:50.996
These are your James Bond!

1376
01:53:56.788 --> 01:54:00.996
Bandu Boss, I'll be there. Tell me when.

1377
01:54:01.163 --> 01:54:04.246
Last day of Ganesha festival.

1378
01:54:04.580 --> 01:54:06.080
Done.

1379
01:54:08.288 --> 01:54:12.913
Your son graces events by gangsters.

1380
01:54:13.580 --> 01:54:16.496
Cops have 60 such phone taps.

1381
01:54:16.913 --> 01:54:20.413
He's not focused on work.
His last 12 films tanked.


1382
01:54:20.913 --> 01:54:26.496
His bail can be revoked.
In short, he's finished!


1383
01:54:27.080 --> 01:54:30.830
Then state that with conviction.

1384
01:54:31.955 --> 01:54:35.163
Put a full stop. 
Not a question mark.

1385
01:54:49.621 --> 01:54:53.663
Mr. Editor, don't write his obituary yet.

1386
01:54:53.746 --> 01:54:55.663
My son will rise again.

1387
01:54:56.288 --> 01:54:59.455
I'll prove you wrong.

1388
01:54:59.788 --> 01:55:01.955
I'm around, and so are you.

1389
01:55:02.121 --> 01:55:03.330
We'll meet again.

1390
01:55:08.955 --> 01:55:13.996
A lousy editor writing me off
was unacceptable to dad.


1391
01:55:14.580 --> 01:55:18.705
He resolved to get
my life back on track.

1392
01:55:18.871 --> 01:55:23.246
If you hobnob with gangsters,
won't the press hound you?


1393
01:55:23.913 --> 01:55:25.330
Gangster? Who, Dad?

1394
01:55:27.788 --> 01:55:29.038
Bandu Boss.

1395
01:55:30.121 --> 01:55:32.121
Aren't you attending his event?

1396
01:55:33.913 --> 01:55:37.371
What's the option? 
They're dangerous.

1397
01:55:38.246 --> 01:55:39.455
Don't go.

1398
01:55:39.788 --> 01:55:42.913
They'll kill me. 
They shot Gulshan Kumar.

1399
01:55:43.163 --> 01:55:46.080
-Fired at Rakesh Roshan.
-Don't go, sonny.


1400
01:55:46.455 --> 01:55:50.205
If the snoopy press
ensures my safety, I won't go.


1401
01:56:11.413 --> 01:56:12.663
Why are we here, Dad?

1402
01:56:12.746 --> 01:56:15.871
When I was to marry your mom,

1403
01:56:16.080 --> 01:56:21.121
a notorious don... 
Mastan, got livid.

1404
01:56:21.913 --> 01:56:24.705
"Nargis is the pride
of the Muslim community."


1405
01:56:25.371 --> 01:56:28.371
"If a Hindu marries her,
we'll slaughter him."


1406
01:56:28.871 --> 01:56:30.955
I called him and said...

1407
01:56:32.121 --> 01:56:35.621
"Let's meet and talk."

1408
01:56:35.788 --> 01:56:40.580
He agreed. 1 a.m... right here.

1409
01:56:41.996 --> 01:56:44.663
-You came here alone?
-No.


1410
01:56:45.163 --> 01:56:47.080
My Master was with me.

1411
01:56:47.621 --> 01:56:49.955
-Which one?
-Sahir Ludhianvi.


1412
01:56:50.538 --> 01:56:53.538
I reached an hour earlier.

1413
01:56:53.955 --> 01:56:57.580
I let Sahir's song
play in my mind on loop.


1414
01:56:58.205 --> 01:57:04.038
When the don arrived,
I said, "I love Nargis deeply."


1415
01:57:04.871 --> 01:57:06.413
"I want to marry her."

1416
01:57:06.913 --> 01:57:09.163
"And I'll keep her happy forever."

1417
01:57:09.663 --> 01:57:13.580
"If to love someone is wrong, shoot me."

1418
01:57:13.871 --> 01:57:16.996
"If right, give me a hug."

1419
01:57:17.580 --> 01:57:19.038
On our wedding day,

1420
01:57:19.413 --> 01:57:21.621
the biggest bouquet...

1421
01:57:23.038 --> 01:57:24.121
came from Mastan!

1422
01:57:26.705 --> 01:57:29.663
-What song was it, Dad?
-Will you sing it?


1423
01:57:30.705 --> 01:57:32.705
Sing along with me.

1424
01:57:35.330 --> 01:57:38.955
Vicious or vile, let no power

1425
01:57:39.038 --> 01:57:41.580
Ever let you cower

1426
01:57:41.788 --> 01:57:45.080
-Dad, not here.
-Come on, catch the beat.


1427
01:57:46.080 --> 01:57:49.746
Vicious or vile, let no power

1428
01:57:49.871 --> 01:57:52.746
Ever let you cower

1429
01:57:53.371 --> 01:58:00.371
Look evil in the eye
Your head held high


1430
01:58:00.871 --> 01:58:07.663
So what if this be your last breath?

1431
01:58:08.455 --> 01:58:15.163
Rejoice, you never died before your death!

1432
01:58:24.288 --> 01:58:30.580
Sonny, go... let Bandu Boss have it.

1433
01:58:30.996 --> 01:58:32.830
He'll never call again.

1434
01:58:32.913 --> 01:58:36.663
Break

1435
01:58:36.746 --> 01:58:40.621
Every shackle

1436
01:58:42.705 --> 01:58:48.621
Smith each into

1437
01:58:49.580 --> 01:58:53.080
A sword

1438
01:58:54.455 --> 01:58:55.496
Stop!

1439
01:58:59.830 --> 01:59:01.038
Hey, the great Sanju!

1440
01:59:01.163 --> 01:59:03.205
Boss, look who's here.

1441
01:59:04.788 --> 01:59:06.121
The star!

1442
01:59:06.746 --> 01:59:08.496
Welcome!

1443
01:59:09.205 --> 01:59:12.705
No calendar at home?
You're ten days early!


1444
01:59:12.788 --> 01:59:16.580
Welcome... sit.

1445
01:59:20.371 --> 01:59:22.746
May I speak in private?

1446
01:59:22.830 --> 01:59:23.996
In private?

1447
01:59:24.580 --> 01:59:26.413
They're family.

1448
01:59:27.871 --> 01:59:29.371
Close your ears.

1449
01:59:31.413 --> 01:59:35.538
We reject condoms
and eject large families.


1450
01:59:36.663 --> 01:59:38.496
Now tell me.

1451
01:59:41.121 --> 01:59:43.163
I can't attend the Ganesha festival.

1452
01:59:45.413 --> 01:59:46.996
Are you sloshed?

1453
01:59:47.413 --> 01:59:49.496
I've already announced to the world.

1454
01:59:49.621 --> 01:59:51.705
My parents are joining, too.

1455
01:59:51.830 --> 01:59:54.496
I too have a father. 
He disapproves.

1456
01:59:57.121 --> 01:59:59.330
He approves when you meet
the gangs in Dubai?


1457
02:00:00.413 --> 02:00:03.246
Did I have a choice? I was scared.

1458
02:00:05.538 --> 02:00:07.496
You ain't scared of me?

1459
02:00:08.621 --> 02:00:10.663
Boys, show him fear.

1460
02:00:32.371 --> 02:00:34.705
Wanna see your brains?

1461
02:00:37.871 --> 02:00:40.955
Blow them out, but first... hear me out.

1462
02:00:42.580 --> 02:00:47.621
If I attend your event,
the press will print...


1463
02:00:47.913 --> 02:00:49.080
"Sanju
-Gangsters Romance."

1464
02:00:49.621 --> 02:00:53.830
If I don't attend, "Gang kills Sanju."

1465
02:00:54.080 --> 02:00:56.121
Either ways, it'll make headlines.

1466
02:00:56.330 --> 02:01:00.330
But, the second headline
won't shame my dad.


1467
02:01:00.913 --> 02:01:02.538
He'll cry gallons.

1468
02:01:03.163 --> 02:01:06.871
But when he faces the world,
his head will be held high.


1469
02:01:07.538 --> 02:01:09.246
Not bowed down in shame.

1470
02:01:11.455 --> 02:01:14.955
If this makes sense... fine.

1471
02:01:18.288 --> 02:01:19.413
If not, shoot me.

1472
02:01:22.955 --> 02:01:25.121
-Boss...
-Shut up!


1473
02:01:31.330 --> 02:01:32.705
I'll leave now.

1474
02:01:33.496 --> 02:01:35.788
If I've overstepped, I'm sorry.

1475
02:01:59.663 --> 02:02:02.663
Bandu Boss never called.

1476
02:02:03.746 --> 02:02:05.496
But he showed up!

1477
02:02:12.080 --> 02:02:13.996
It's a family tradition.

1478
02:02:14.413 --> 02:02:16.705
No murders during the Ganesha fest.

1479
02:02:17.371 --> 02:02:19.330
Decided to kill you after the fest.

1480
02:02:19.788 --> 02:02:21.788
These ten days, 
I only thought of you.

1481
02:02:22.371 --> 02:02:26.371
You risked life to keep
your dad's head unbowed.


1482
02:02:26.788 --> 02:02:29.871
Who does such a stupid thing?

1483
02:02:29.955 --> 02:02:33.080
Head, a few degrees up or down,
what bloody difference?


1484
02:02:35.371 --> 02:02:37.746
I prayed to the Lord for you.

1485
02:02:38.121 --> 02:02:40.580
Told him, "He's one gutsy guy."

1486
02:02:40.830 --> 02:02:44.371
"Help him. Get his charges dropped."

1487
02:02:44.788 --> 02:02:46.871
The Lord said, "Bandu Boss, done!"

1488
02:02:47.996 --> 02:02:49.205
Here are the offerings.

1489
02:02:52.955 --> 02:02:54.538
Success guaranteed!

1490
02:02:54.746 --> 02:02:56.580
-Lord Ganesha...
-Glory be thine!


1491
02:02:56.705 --> 02:02:58.496
Be thine!

1492
02:02:59.246 --> 02:03:00.913
Stay in touch.

1493
02:03:01.121 --> 02:03:02.121
Let's go.

1494
02:03:08.496 --> 02:03:12.163
Get Bandu Boss teary-eyed often.

1495
02:03:12.330 --> 02:03:14.288
Free sweets will follow.

1496
02:03:15.413 --> 02:03:16.580
Sir, it's the director.

1497
02:03:20.371 --> 02:03:21.705
Yes, bro.

1498
02:03:21.788 --> 02:03:23.580
Where are you? 
We are ready to shoot.

1499
02:03:23.663 --> 02:03:26.996
Insane traffic on the highway.

1500
02:03:27.788 --> 02:03:29.830
A truck hit a car.

1501
02:03:32.163 --> 02:03:35.538
Hey, move that taxi.

1502
02:03:36.288 --> 02:03:37.705
Listen.

1503
02:03:37.955 --> 02:03:39.371
I've called the landline.

1504
02:03:42.871 --> 02:03:44.621
Landline's for all and sundry.

1505
02:03:44.705 --> 02:03:46.663
You're my bro, always call on my cell.

1506
02:03:46.746 --> 02:03:49.330
We missed the sunrise shot.

1507
02:03:49.746 --> 02:03:52.288
Shoot it at sunset.

1508
02:03:52.413 --> 02:03:54.371
The audience won't know shit.

1509
02:03:54.455 --> 02:03:57.705
Now hang up or we'll miss the sunset.

1510
02:03:59.163 --> 02:04:02.371
Time to introduce you to Master no. 2.

1511
02:04:03.663 --> 02:04:06.996
He'll teach you to respect work.

1512
02:04:07.371 --> 02:04:09.746
If you keep missing sunrise shoots,

1513
02:04:09.830 --> 02:04:12.288
the sun will set on your career.

1514
02:04:12.538 --> 02:04:15.413
Do good work and the press
will change its opinion, too.


1515
02:04:16.205 --> 02:04:17.871
Good work?

1516
02:04:18.205 --> 02:04:19.621
With such trashy scripts.

1517
02:04:21.580 --> 02:04:22.996
Here...

1518
02:04:24.080 --> 02:04:27.746
Kinky King, Rowdy Romeo...

1519
02:04:28.371 --> 02:04:31.788
Munnabhai MBBS, 
Punky Prince...

1520
02:04:31.871 --> 02:04:33.746
Aamir and Shah Rukh grab the best.

1521
02:04:34.121 --> 02:04:38.038
-Do you read these scripts?
-Cover to cover.


1522
02:04:38.163 --> 02:04:41.080
All read and rejected.

1523
02:04:41.538 --> 02:04:44.330
"Munnabhai MBBS." Read this one?

1524
02:04:44.455 --> 02:04:46.871
-I did.
-What's the story?


1525
02:04:49.371 --> 02:04:50.788
It's trash!

1526
02:04:52.288 --> 02:04:54.663
There's a hospital...

1527
02:04:54.788 --> 02:04:59.205
where a patient gets murdered...
every day!


1528
02:04:59.788 --> 02:05:03.663
Then kidneys are stolen.
It's a horror story.


1529
02:05:03.913 --> 02:05:05.496
I need a family film.

1530
02:05:05.788 --> 02:05:09.163
The draft I read has no murders.

1531
02:05:10.371 --> 02:05:15.580
-Why did you read it?
-I'm playing your father in this film.


1532
02:05:16.163 --> 02:05:19.663
I'll set up Master
no. 2 in your car.

1533
02:05:19.746 --> 02:05:23.580
Listen to the song
on loop at full volume.

1534
02:05:31.455 --> 02:05:34.371
If you shirk from work

1535
02:05:36.913 --> 02:05:39.955
You get no perk, you jerk

1536
02:05:40.038 --> 02:05:41.788
Turn it off!

1537
02:05:41.871 --> 02:05:44.746
It's Mr. Dutt's order to play this song
the whole month.


1538
02:05:44.830 --> 02:05:48.330
And check that you lip sync.

1539
02:05:54.788 --> 02:05:56.996
If you shirk from work

1540
02:05:57.080 --> 02:05:58.455
I am singing.

1541
02:05:59.663 --> 02:06:02.330
You get no perk, you jerk

1542
02:06:02.788 --> 02:06:05.371
If duties you duck
You land up in muck


1543
02:06:05.663 --> 02:06:08.330
On bankruptcy's brink
